  "response_text": "Against a bright baseball stadium backdrop, a large blue bottle of All Stainlifter laundry detergent stands upright on green grass near the infield dirt. It has a yellow cap, a built-in handle on the right, and a yellow label with the large lowercase “all” logo and “stainlifter” beneath it. Bold promotional text then fills the center over the bottle: “NOW! IN-WASH PRE-TREATERS” and, below it, “FOR BETTER STAIN REMOVAL.” Small fine print near the lower right says it is “specially formulated with added enzymes.”\n\nThe scene shifts to a Little League baseball field. Youth players in full uniforms are in action around home plate, with Little League Baseball logos visible on the dark green outfield wall. A pitcher in a yellow jersey has just thrown toward a batter in a light blue jersey, while a catcher crouches behind the plate. The commercial then focuses on the kind of messy play that creates stains. A youth fielder in a green jersey, red sleeves, white pants, and a green cap dives low across the grass, stretching one arm toward a rolling baseball. His white pants and jersey scrape the turf as dirt and grass kick up around him. Another player in a matching green uniform stands behind him with a glove, watching the play.\n\nAnother youth player in a light blue jersey and white pants dives and slides across the outfield grass. He lands on his side, then rolls with his legs flipping upward, his white pants dragging across the green turf. The emphasis is on the contact between the clean white uniform fabric and the grass, suggesting heavy grass stains from the slide.\n\nAt home plate, a runner in a red jersey and white pants charges in and slides feet-first through the dirt. A catcher in a green uniform reaches to tag him as dust rises from the brown batter’s box area. The runner ends up low on the ground under the catcher’s legs, and the catcher bends over him with glove extended. A baseball bat lies on the dirt to the right of the plate, adding to t