rrounded by blue liquid and small bubbles. More blue All-branded spheres appear and move over a white mesh-like fabric surface covered with green grass-stain particles. The spheres roll and float along the fabric while tiny green specks scatter, visually representing the detergent attacking or lifting stains. Small disclaimer text appears along the bottom during this sequence, including a reference to a grass stain on polyester fabric and washing conditions.\n\nOn a plain white background, an unbranded orange detergent bottle with a dark blue cap appears. The word “Detergent” is printed on it in blue-green letters. A blue tub labeled “BOOSTER” slides in beside it, creating a comparison setup. Small fine print at the bottom explains that the comparison is based on pre-treating and washing with All Stainlifter versus washing with a leading value detergent and leading booster combined. Then the blue All Stainlifter bottle enters from the right, while bold blue text above reads “MORE CLEANING POWER!” The orange detergent and blue booster slide away, leaving the All bottle alone under the “MORE CLEANING POWER!” message.\n\nFinally, the product returns to the bright laundry-room display. The All bottle stands centered on the white counter with the baseball helmet on the left, folded clean clothes on the right, and a baseball in front. Across the top, the slogan appears in lowercase: “give us your worst, we’ll give it our” followed by the small All logo, completing the phrase visually as “all.” A Little League Baseball seal appears near the lower left beside the helmet. The closing image is clean and orderly, with the blue bottle prominent against the white background and the baseball items framing it.",
